HAVANA, April 25 (Xinhua) -- Cuba on Monday recorded 237 COVID-19 infections with no death in the last day, the lowest daily count of the year, bringing national tally to 1,101,968 with 8,525 deaths, the Ministry of Public Health said. So far, 9.9 million of Cuba's 11.2 million residents have been fully vaccinated against the virus, while 6.5 million have received a booster dose. The national vaccination campaign is being carried out with three Cuban-made vaccines, namely Abdala, Soberana-02 and Soberana Plus.  â– 